reviewText: I miss Tom Barnaby dreadfully, but life goes on and thankfully so do the Midsomer mysteries. My two favorites of this series fifteen were "Dark Rider", a spooky headless-horseman type story, and "Schooled In Murder", wickedly combining a girls' school with Midsomer Blue cheese! Not Tom Barnaby, but still excellent. Sykes, the Barnabys' dog, is the icing on the cake. I'm glad the series is still being made. Cheers!
It was good as a continuation of the series! The format was acceptable and the discs were colorful! The characters colorful!
